+# agent-lifecycle SELF-TEST
+
+Quick validation that this skill's substrate is load-bearing.
+
+## Run
+
+```bash
+bash ~/.claude/skills/agent-lifecycle/scripts/self-test.sh           # human-readable
+bash ~/.claude/skills/agent-lifecycle/scripts/self-test.sh --json    # machine envelope
+```
+
+Expected: exit 0 with `status=pass`, `py_compile=pass`,
+`deploy_json_smoke=pass`. Schema: `agent-lifecycle.self-test.v1`.
+
+## What it checks
+
+1. `python3 -m py_compile scripts/lifecycle_manager.py` — catches
+   syntax breakage in the skill's Python entrypoint without executing
+   the module.
+2. `python3 scripts/lifecycle_manager.py --deploy --json` — the
+   canonical deploy smoke. Asserts the envelope has
+   `operation=deploy`, `status=completed`, and at least one finding
+   with `summary.total_findings >= 1`.
+
+The wrapper exits non-zero when either check fails so
+`~/.claude/skills/skill-builder/scripts/validate-skill.sh` gets a
+truthful signal.
+
+## See also
+
+- `scripts/lifecycle_manager.py` — Python entrypoint (canonical
+  per-op coverage).
+- `SKILL.md` — full lifecycle doctrine.
+- `~/.claude/skills/skill-builder/scripts/validate-skill.sh` — fleet
+  validator that requires this skill to ship at least one `.sh` file.
